I’m like, bro, I’m not racking up frequent flyer miles to send YOU my phone! Thought I was chatting with AI, but nah, he swore he’s human. Skeptical, I demanded a manager. Manager swoops in, insists the label’s fine for air shipping—despite me sending pics of it screaming 'UPS Ground' in bold. After some back-and-forth photo evidence, he’s like, 'Uh, let me check with the big bosses. We’ll figure this out in 2-3 days.' So here I am, chilling in paradise, waiting for Google to decide if my phone can catch a flight. Aloha-level absurdity!
